'''Ethernet''' is a family of [[Data frame|frame]]-based [[computer network]]ing technologies for [[local area network]]s (LANs). The name comes from the physical concept of the [[Luminiferous aether|ether]]. It defines a number of wiring and signaling standards for the [[physical layer]], through means of network access at the [[Media Access Control]] (MAC)/[[Data Link Layer]], and a common addressing format.
